# Feature Catalog Maintenance Rule

## File
`docs/FEATURES.md` – single source of truth for all app features, tech stack, integrations, and component inventory.

## When to Update

### 1. New feature added
- Add an entry to the **Feature Overview** table (increment #, pick the right screen, set "Added" date)
- Add a **Detailed Feature Description** section in the appropriate category group
- If it introduces a new API route, add to the **API Routes** table
- If it introduces a new DB table, add to the **Database Tables** section
- If it introduces a new reusable component, add to the **Component Library** table
- Update the **"What Changed"** section at the bottom with today's date and a one-liner

### 2. Feature changed significantly
- Update the relevant detail section (new capabilities, changed behavior)
- Add a line to the **"What Changed"** section

### 3. Feature removed or deprecated
- Remove from (or mark deprecated in) the **Feature Overview** table
- Update the detail section with a deprecation note
- Add a line to the **"What Changed"** section

### 4. Tech stack or integration changed
- Update the **Tech Stack** table (new library, version change, removed dependency)
- Update the **Key Integrations** table if a service is added or removed

### 5. Version bump
- Update the **Version** in the header when `package.json` version changes

## Format to Preserve
- Overview table uses sequential `#` numbering
- Detail sections grouped by domain: Core, AI, Voice & Image, Google, Analytics, Settings
- Each detail section includes: **Screen**, **Files**, **Tables** (if any), bullet list of capabilities
- Component Library is a simple 3-column table (Component | File | Purpose)
- API Routes is a 3-column table (Route | Method | Purpose)
- "What Changed" at the bottom is a date-grouped log

## When Not to Update
- Pure refactors that don't change user-visible behavior
- Bug fixes that don't add/remove capability
- Styling/theme tweaks within existing feature scope
- If the user explicitly says not to update FEATURES.md
